        "title": "fix(telegram): delete approval message after resolution instead of clearing buttons",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen a Telegram exec approval was resolved, `clearPendingActions` only cleared the inline keyboard — the approval prompt text remained visible in chat even after the user approved or denied.\n\nThis fix uses the approval runtime's built-in `kind: \"delete\"` final-action seam:\n\n1. **`buildResolvedResult`**: Returns `{ kind: \"delete\" }` (was `{ kind: \"clear-actions\" }`), causing the shared runtime to call `transport.deleteEntry`\n2. **`transport.deleteEntry`** (new): Calls `deleteMessageTelegram` to fully remove the approval bubble\n3. **`clearPendingActions`** (restored): Only clears the inline keyboard for **expired** approvals — keeps the prompt text visible so chat history is preserved\n4. **Type safety**: Added `deleteMessage` to `TelegramExecApprovalHandlerDeps`\n\nFixes #56286\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Telegram exec approval bubble was not dismissed after clicking approve/deny — only the buttons were cleared, leaving the prompt text.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node v24.13.0, Linux x86_64\n- **Test framework**: Vitest v4.1.8 (5 approval handler tests)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\n RUN  v4.1.8\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  5 passed (5)  ← 2 original + 3 new\n   Start at  10:42:46\n   Duration  17.54s\n```\n\n**New tests added** (3):\n\n1. `returns delete for resolved and clear-actions for expired (regression #56286)` — Verifies `buildResolvedResult` → `{ kind: \"delete\" }` and `buildExpiredResult` → `{ kind: \"clear-actions\" }`\n\n2. `deletes the approval message via transport.deleteEntry (regression #56286)` — Verifies `deleteEntry` calls `deleteMessageTelegram` with correct chatId, messageId, and options\n\n3. `clears only the inline keyboard on expired, not delete (regression #56286)` — Verifies `clearPendingActions` calls `editMessageReplyMarkupTelegram` with empty buttons `[]` (preserves text) instead of deleting\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Resolved approvals are fully deleted from chat. Expired approvals only lose their buttons — the prompt text remains as chat history.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Telegram bot with real exec approval flow. The change is architecture-level (switching final-action kinds) and testable at the adapter layer via mocks.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```bash\n# Targeted approval handler tests (5/5)\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  5 passed (5)\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` — resolved approval bubbles now fully disappear instead of leaving text behind)\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- The `transport.deleteEntry` call relies on entry having `chatId`/`messageId` from `deliverPending`; if that contract changes, the delete fails gracefully\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- `deleteMessageTelegram` already handles delete-no-op errors gracefully (existing production code)\n- `deleteEntry` falls back to `deleteMessageTelegram` if `deps?.deleteMessage` is absent\n- `clearPendingActions` (expired path) is unchanged from original behavior — only clears buttons\n\n## Changes from review feedback\n\nPer ClawSweeper review on 2026-06-19:\n\n1. ✅ **[P1] Keep clear-actions from deleting approval content**: `clearPendingActions` is now button-only (calls `editMessageReplyMarkupTelegram` with `[]`). Resolved approvals use `kind: \"delete\"` + `transport.deleteEntry` instead.\n\n2. ✅ **[P1] Keep Telegram approval deps type-safe**: Added `deleteMessage` property to `TelegramExecApprovalHandlerDeps`. Restored `editMessageReplyMarkupTelegram` import. No type mismatches remain.\n\n3. ✅ **[P1] Add focused cleanup tests**: Tests cover `buildResolvedResult`, `buildExpiredResult`, `transport.deleteEntry`, and `interactions.clearPendingActions` for resolved and expired paths.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review",
